Submitted By:            Combined: Douglas R. Reno (build fix) + still image + tune fix + YUV444
Date:                    2026-03-21
Initial Package Version: 1.21.2
Upstream Status:         Pending
Origin:                  Upstream (PR #1680) + three additional fixes
Description:             Fixes building libheif with SVT-AV1 4.0 and later.
                         Three changes on top of the original build fix:

                         1. Still image mode (SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0):
                            pred_structure=2, hierarchical_levels=0,
                            intra_period_length=-1, fps=1/1.
                            Note: avif=true is intentionally omitted — SVT-AV1 4.x
                            avif mode only supports YUV420, conflicting with YUV444.
                            intra_period_length=-1 already produces still_picture=1
                            in the AV1 sequence header as required by AVIF spec.

                         2. tune=SSIM fallback to PSNR (SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0):
                            SVT-AV1 4.x requires CRF for tune=SSIM but libheif uses
                            CQP. Sharp passes tune=ssim by default for .heif() calls
                            which crashes the encoder. Fall back silently to PSNR.

                         3. YUV444 by default (SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0):
                            SVT-AV1 4.x supports YUV444 when avif mode is not active.
                            Returning heif_chroma_444 eliminates the even-dimension
                            requirement of YUV420, so odd-sized images no longer
                            produce a clap box with fractional pixel offsets that
                            Firefox rejects per AVIF spec. Sharp defaults to
                            chromaSubsampling='4:4:4' for AVIF, matching caller intent.

--- libheif-1.21.2.orig/libheif/plugins/encoder_svt.cc	2026-03-21 20:14:04.359363316 +0000
+++ libheif-1.21.2/libheif/plugins/encoder_svt.cc	2026-03-21 20:14:25.189435948 +0000
@@ -646,16 +646,27 @@ static void svt_set_default_parameters(v
 void svt_query_input_colorspace(heif_colorspace* colorspace, heif_chroma* chroma)
 {
   *colorspace = heif_colorspace_YCbCr;
+  // SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0 supports YUV444 when avif mode is NOT active.
+  // 4:4:4 eliminates the even-dimension requirement of YUV420, so odd-sized
+  // images no longer produce a clap box with fractional offsets that Firefox
+  // rejects. Sharp defaults to chromaSubsampling='4:4:4' for AVIF, matching
+  // caller intent. Pass chromaSubsampling:'4:2:0' in sharp to use 4:2:0.
+#if SVT_AV1_CHECK_VERSION(4, 0, 0)
+  *chroma = heif_chroma_444;
+#else
   *chroma = heif_chroma_420;
+#endif
 }
 
 
